-- Tepco to scrap first four nuclear reactors at Fukushima Daiichi
-- 
-- Fri May 20, 2011 2:36am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/20/us-japan-nuclear-tepco-idUSTRE74J13G20110520

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Tokyo Electric Power Co said on Friday it has decided to scrap the first four reactors of its Fukushima Daiichi nuclear plant, which was crippled by a massive earthquake in March. 

 The utility also said it has decided to suspend development of the Fukushima Daiichi No. 7 and No. 8 reactors. The company said its capital investment in fiscal 2010/11 ended in March totaled 614.9 billion yen ($7.5 billion), down by 77.9 billion yen from its original plan. ($1 = 81.610 Japanese Yen) (Reporting by Osamu Tsukimori; Editing by  Chris Gallagher )